The last is yet to be heard of the unrest trailing the new appointments into the  Board of the Niger Delta Development Commission, NDDC,  as two opposing groups staged protests in Port Harcourt, the Rivers state capital recently.  PORT HAR-COURT— Hundreds of Ijaw Youth Congress, IYC, members, yesterday, stormed the head office of Niger Delta Development Commission, NDDC, in Port Harcourt, Rivers State, protesting alleged Federal Government’s plan to extend the tenure of the current board of the commission. December 22, 2017 In "News" President Muhammadu Buhari has been urged to confirm the appointment of Mrs Ibim Semenitari, as substantive Managing Director of Niger Delta Development Commission, NDDC. March 23, 2016 In "News" Niger Delta Development Commission, NDDC, has assured that it will change its negative image of a corrupt institution. June 6, 2017 In "News"